72]]\n| [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| [[List of Italian constituencies (1946\u20131994)#Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone|Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Christian Democracy (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Christian Democracy (Italy)|DC]]\n| 367,235\n| {{tick|15}} '''Elected'''\n|-\n! [[1976 Italian general election|1976]]\n| [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| [[List of Italian constituencies (1946\u20131994)#Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone|Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Christian Democracy (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Christian Democracy (Italy)|DC]]\n| 191,593\n| {{tick|15}} '''Elected'''\n|-\n! [[1979 Italian general election|1979]]\n| [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| [[List of Italian constituencies (1946\u20131994)#Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone|Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Christian Democracy (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Christian Democracy (Italy)|DC]]\n| 302,745\n| {{tick|15}} '''Elected'''\n|-\n! [[1983 Italian general election|1983]]\n| [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| [[List of Italian constituencies (1946\u20131994)#Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone|Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Christian Democracy (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Christian Democracy (Italy)|DC]]\n| 206,944\n| {{tick|15}} '''Elected'''\n|-\n! [[1987 Italian general election|1987]]\n| [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]\n| [[List of Italian constituencies (1946\u20131994)#Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone|Rome\u2013Viterbo\u2013Latina\u2013Frosinone]]\n| bgcolor=\"{{Christian Democracy (Italy)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Christian Democracy (Italy)|DC]]\n| 329,599\n| {{tick|15}} '''Elected'''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Wilsford, David, ed. ''Political leaders of contemporary Western Europe: a biographical dictionary'' (Greenwood, 1995) pp 8\u201316.\n* Giuseppe Leone, \"Federico II Re di Prussia e Giulio Andreotti \u2013 Due modi diversi di concepire la politica\", su \"Ricorditi di me...\", in \"Lecco 2000\", gennaio 1996. {{in lang|it}}\n\n===Primary sources===\n* Andreotti, Giulio. \"Foreign policy in the Italian democracy.\" ''Political Science Quarterly'' 109#3 (1994): 529-537. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/2152618 in JSTOR]\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20051122115024/http://www.univ-tlse2.fr/grhi/cahier/select_articles/foro.htm ''\"Les proc\u00e8s Andreotti en Italie\"''] (\"The Andreotti trials in Italy\") by Philippe Foro, published by University of [[Toulouse]] II, ''Groupe de recherche sur l'histoire imm\u00e9diate'' (Study group on contemporary history) {{in lang|fr}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100110055636/http://www.luckyred.it/ildivo/sito_en/home.html Il Divo] a Paolo Sorrentino Film\n*{{C-SPAN}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|it-lwr}}\n|-\n{{s-non|reason=Parliament re-established}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Member of Parliament]] for [[Province of Rome|Rome]]<br/>Legislatures: CA, I, II, III, IV, V, VI, VII, VIII, IX, X|years=1946\u20131991}}\n{{s-non|reason=Title jointly held}}\n{{s-par|it-upr}}\n|-\n{{s-non|reason=Presidential appointment}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Senator for life]]<br/>Legislatures: X, XI, XII, XIII, XIV, XV, XVI, XVII|years=1991\u20132013}}\n{{s-non|reason=Died in office}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Amintore Fanfani]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Italian Minister of the Interior|Minister of the Interior]]|years=1954}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Mario Scelba]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Roberto Tremelloni]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Minister of Finance|years=1955\u20131958}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Luigi Preti]]}}\n{{Succession box|title=Minister of Treasury|before=[[Giuseppe Medici]]|after=[[Fernando Tambroni]]|years=1958\u20131959}}\n{{Succession box|title=[[Italian Minister of Defence|Minister of Defence]]|before=