, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"TDS All-American\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Glademir|Mendoza}}\n| [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|American Athletic Conference]] Rookie-Team All-Conference\n| {{dts|November 12, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"AAC Awards\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Yannik|Oettl}}\n| [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|American Athletic Conference]] Goalkeeper of the Year\n| {{dts|November 12, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"AAC Awards\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Yannik|Oettl}}\n| [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|American Athletic Conference]] First-Team All-Conference\n| {{dts|November 12, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"AAC Awards\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Louis|Perez|Louis Perez (French footballer)}}\n| [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|American Athletic Conference]] Second-Team All-Conference\n| {{dts|November 12, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"AAC Awards\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Yori|Sorokin}}\n| [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|American Athletic Conference]] Co-Midfielder of the Year\n| {{dts|November 12, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"AAC Awards\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Yori|Sorokin}}\n| [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|American Athletic Conference]] First-Team All-Conference\n| {{dts|November 12, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"AAC Awards\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Yori|Sorokin}}\n| ''[[TopDrawerSoccer.com|Top Drawer Soccer]]'' Second-Team [[2019 NCAA Men's Soccer All-Americans|All-American]] \n| {{dts|December 17, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"TDS All-American\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Gino|Vivi}}\n| [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|American Athletic Conference]] Rookie of the Year\n| {{dts|November 12, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"AAC Awards\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Gino|Vivi}}\n| [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|American Athletic Conference]] Rookie-Team All-Conference\n| {{dts|November 12, 2019}}\n| <ref name=\"AAC Awards\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Gino|Vivi}}\n| ''[[TopDrawerSoccer.com|Top Drawer Soccer]]'' Third-Team Freshman [[2019 NCAA Men's Soccer All-Americans|All-American]] \n| {{dts|December 17, 2019}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.topdrawersoccer.com/college-soccer/college-national-freshmen-top-100/men/2019|title=College Soccer Player Rankings - Freshman - Men's Freshmen Top 100 - 2019|last=|first=|date=|website=TopDrawerSoccer.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-12-29}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://ucfknights.com/index.aspx?path=msoc UCF Soccer]\n{{UCF Knights men's soccer navbox}}\n{{2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season}}\n{{2019 NCAA Division I men's soccer season}}\n{{2019 in American soccer}}\n\n[[Category:UCF Knights men's soccer seasons|2019]]\n[[Category:2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season|UCF Knights]]\n[[Category:American men's college soccer teams 2019 season|UCF Knights]]\n[[Category:2019 in sports in Florida|UCF Knights men's soccer]]\n[[Category:2019 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Tournament participants|UCF Knights]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| sport = soccer\n| year = 2019\n| team = UCF Knights\n| logo = UCF Knights logo.svg\n| logo_size = 150\n| logo_alt = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| conference = American Athletic Conference\n| short_conf = American \n| record = 15\u20133\u20132\n| conf_record = 6\u20130\u20131\n| NSCAARank = 10\n| TDSRank = 10\n| head_coach = [[Scott Calabrese]]\n| hc_year = 3rd\n| asst_coach1 = Paul Souders\n| ac1_year = 4th\n| asst_coach2 = Jamie Davies\n| ac2_year = 2nd\n| captain  = Cal Jennings\n| captain2 = Richard Amon\n| captain3 = [[Yannik Oettl]]\n| stadium = [[UCF Soccer and Track Stadium]]\n| champion = American Athletic Regular Season Champions\n| tourney        = [[2019 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]\n| tourney_result = Third Round\n| prev_year = 2018\n| next_year = 2020\n}}\n{{2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer standings}}\nThe '''2019 UCF Knights men's soccer''' team represented the [[University of Central Florida]] during the [[2019 NCAA Division I men's soccer season]] and the [[2019 American Athletic Conference men's soccer season]]. The regular season began on August 30 and concluded on November 5. It was the program's 44th season fielding a men's varsity soccer team, and their 7th season in the AAC. The 2019 season was [[Scott Calabrese]]'s third year as head coach for the program.\n\nUCF finished the season with a 15\u20133\u20132 overall record and a 6\u20130\u20131 conference record, best in the AAC. The Knights advanced to the finals of the [[American Athletic Conference Men's Soccer Tournament|AAC Tournament]] where they fell to [[2019 SMU Mustangs men's soccer team|SMU]] for the third consecutive year. They received an at-large bid to the the [[2019 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Tournament|NCAA Tournament]] and advanced to the third round where they were defeated by SMU. \n\n== Background ==\n{{main|2018 UCF Knights men's soccer team}}\nThe Knights are coming off a 13\u20133\u20133 season where they finished 5\u20131\u20131 in AAC play, earning them their first [[American Athletic Conference]] regular season title. In the [[2018 American Athletic Conference Men's Soccer Tournament]], UCF lost to [[SMU Mustangs men's soccer|SMU]] in [[penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty kicks]], 4\u20135 after a 1\u20131 draw in regulation and extra time. UCF earned an at-large berth into the [[2018 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Tournament]], where they were one of the 16 seeded teams (out of 48 teams total) given the 14 seed. It was UCF's first NCAA Tournament appearance since 2011. With the seed, they earned a bye into the second round where they hosted the winner of Washington and Lipscomb. Lipscomb beat Washington in penalties, and also ended up beating the Knights in overtime, thus ending the season for UCF.\n\nJunior striker, Cal Jennings, lead UCF in goals and assists for 2018 and was named a [[2018 NCAA Men's Soccer All-Americans|consensus All-American]] with [[TopDrawerSoccer.com|Top Drawer Soccer]], ''[[Soccer America]]'', [[United Soccer Coaches]], and CollegeSoccerNews.com all naming him as a first-team All-American.\n\n== Player movement ==\n=== Departures ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; \"\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Name\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Nat.\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Number\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Position\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Height\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Weight\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Year\n! style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Hometown\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|UCF Knights|color=#000000}}\"| Reason for departure\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{sortname|Andreas|Steineger|nolink=1}} || {{flag|NOR}} || 2 || {{sort|2|[[Defender (association football)|DF]]}} || {{height|ft=6|in=4}} || 190 || {{sort|4|Senior}} || [[Oslo|Oslo, NOR]] ||align=\"left\"| Graduated\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{sortname|Zachary|Waitman|nolink=1}} || {{flag|USA}} || 5 || {{sort|2|[[Defender (association football)|DF]]}} || {{height|ft=5|in=8}} || 165 || {{sort|4|Senior}} || [[Montverde, Florida|Montverde, FL]] ||align=\"left\"| Graduated\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{sortname|Jonathan|Dean|nolink=1}} || {{flag|USA}} || 6 || {{sort|3|[[Midfielder|MF]]}} || {{height|ft=5|in=8}} || 155 || {{sort|4|Senior}} || [[Macon, Georgia|Macon, GA]] ||align=\"left\"| Graduated\n|-\n|align=\"left\"| {{sortname|Gorka|Aperribay|nolink=1}} || {{flag|USA}} || 9 || {{sort|4|[[Forward (association football)|FW]]}} || {{height|ft=6|in=1}} || 185 || {{sort|4|S